          },
          {
            "kind": {
              "type": "Section",
              "attrs": {
                "id": null,
                "pairs": {}
              },
              "title": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "text": "Step 8.5: Auto-invoke /document-release"
                }
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "kind": {
                    "type": "Paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "Text",
                        "text": "After the PR is created, automatically sync project documentation. Read the\n`document-release/SKILL.md` skill file (adjacent to this skill's directory) and\nexecute its full workflow:\n\n1. Read the `/document-release` skill: `cat ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/../document-release/SKILL.md`\n2. Follow its instructions — it reads all .md files in the project, cross-references\n   the diff, and updates anything that drifted (README, ARCHITECTURE, CONTRIBUTING,\n   CLAUDE.md, TODOS, etc.)\n3. If any docs were updated, commit the changes and push to the same branch:\n   ```bash\n   git add -A && git commit -m \"docs: sync documentation with shipped changes\" && git push\n   ```\n4. If no docs needed updating, say \"Documentation is current — no updates needed.\"\n\nThis step is automatic. Do not ask the user for confirmation. The goal is zero-friction\ndoc updates — the user runs `/ship` and documentation stays current without a separate command.\n\n---"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "span": {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 0
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "span": {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 0
            }
          },
          {
            "kind": {
              "type": "Section",
              "attrs": {
                "id": null,
                "pairs": {}
              },
              "title": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "text": "Step 8.75: Persist ship metrics"
                }
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "kind": {
                    "type": "Paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "Text",
                        "text": "Log coverage and plan completion data so `/retro` can track trends:\n\n```bash\neval \"$(~/.claude/skills/gstack/bin/gstack-slug 2>/dev/null)\" && mkdir -p ~/.gstack/projects/$SLUG\n```\n\nAppend to `~/.gstack/projects/$SLUG/$BRANCH-reviews.jsonl`:\n\n```bash\necho '{\"skill\":\"ship\",\"timestamp\":\"'\"$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\"'\",\"coverage_pct\":COVERAGE_PCT,\"plan_items_total\":PLAN_TOTAL,\"plan_items_done\":PLAN_DONE,\"verification_result\":\"VERIFY_RESULT\",\"version\":\"VERSION\",\"branch\":\"BRANCH\"}' >> ~/.gstack/projects/$SLUG/$BRANCH-reviews.jsonl\n```\n\nSubstitute from earlier steps:\n- **COVERAGE_PCT**: coverage percentage from Step 3.4 diagram (integer, or -1 if undetermined)\n- **PLAN_TOTAL**: total plan items extracted in Step 3.45 (0 if no plan file)\n- **PLAN_DONE**: count of DONE + CHANGED items from Step 3.45 (0 if no plan file)\n- **VERIFY_RESULT**: \"pass\", \"fail\", or \"skipped\" from Step 3.47\n- **VERSION**: from the VERSION file\n- **BRANCH**: current branch name\n\nThis step is automatic — never skip it, never ask for confirmation.\n\n---"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "span": {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 0
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "span": {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 0
            }
          },
          {
            "kind": {
              "type": "Section",
              "attrs": {
                "id": null,
                "pairs": {}
              },
              "title": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "text": "Important Rules"
                }
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "kind": {
                    "type": "Paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "Text",
                        "text": "- **Never skip tests.** If tests fail, stop.\n- **Never skip the pre-landing review.** If checklist.md is unreadable, stop.\n- **Never force push.** Use regular `git push` only.\n- **Never ask for trivial confirmations** (e.g., \"ready to push?\", \"create PR?\"). DO stop for: version bumps (MINOR/MAJOR), pre-landing review findings (ASK items), and Codex structured review [P1] findings (large diffs only).\n- **Always use the 4-digit version format** from the VERSION file.\n- **Date format in CHANGELOG:** `YYYY-MM-DD`\n- **Split commits for bisectability** — each commit = one logical change.\n- **TODOS.md completion detection must be conservative.** Only mark items as completed when the diff clearly shows the work is done.\n- **Use Greptile reply templates from greptile-triage.md.** Every reply includes evidence (inline diff, code references, re-rank suggestion). Never post vague replies.\n- **Never push without fresh verification evidence.** If code changed after Step 3 tests, re-run before pushing.\n- **Step 3.4 generates coverage tests.** They must pass before committing. Never commit failing tests.\n- **The goal is: user says `/ship`, next thing they see is the review + PR URL + auto-synced docs.**"
                      }
                    ]
